snippet.textDisplay:
Google is genius playing 4d chess on this one.

1. Take an open source OS, strip it down and simplify it. Optimize it for cheap ARM processors.

2. People manufacture it because it's cheap.

3. Google gives it to schools for free.

4. Entire generation of children grow up on it.

5. A pandemic hits and suddenly everyone has to work and school from home. Need to suddenly buy 3 laptops? You ain't going windows.

All this has positioned Google to dominate Windows in terms of percent of users. Windows is going to either have to make much better low end stuff (windows 10 s mode is a joke) or they will have to really focus on the high end.
